## Medium Severity

### 5. Eager Test â€” `OrderProcessor_FullWorkflow_Succeeds`

```csharp
processor.ValidateOrder(order);
processor.CalculateTotal(order);
processor.ApplyDiscount(order, "SAVE10");
processor.ReserveInventory(order);
processor.ProcessPayment(order, new CreditCard("4111111111111111"));
processor.SendConfirmation(order);
processor.UpdateOrderHistory(order);
Assert.AreEqual("Completed", order.Status);
```

**Problem:** 7 distinct production methods in one test. If this fails, you don't know which step broke. Each method deserves its own focused test.

**Fix:** If you need an end-to-end workflow test, keep it but label it as an integration test. Then add focused unit tests for each step:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void ApplyDiscount_ValidCode_ReducesTotal()
{
    var processor = new OrderProcessor(_db, _email, _inventory);
    var order = new Order { Items = { new OrderItem("SKU-1", 2) }, TotalAmount = 100m };

    processor.ApplyDiscount(order, "SAVE10");

    Assert.AreEqual(90m, order.TotalAmount);
}
```

