**`ValidateOrder_NullOrder_ThrowsArgumentNullException`** (line 155) is well-written:
- Uses `Assert.ThrowsException<T>` â€” clean, idiomatic
- Asserts on the specific `ParamName` â€” precise verification
- Single responsibility â€” tests exactly one behavior
- No magic values, no external dependencies

This is a good reference for refactoring the other tests.

