## Prioritized Remediation Plan

| Priority | Test | Smell | Why First |
|----------|------|-------|-----------|
| 1 | `ProcessOrder_CompletesWithoutError` | Assertion-Free | **Actively hiding bugs** â€” test passes no matter what |
| 2 | `ProcessOrder_SetsCorrectStatus` | Conditional Logic | **Untested branch** â€” half the logic is never verified |
| 3 | `ImportOrders_FromCsv_ParsesCorrectly` | Mystery Guest | **Broken everywhere** except one specific machine |
| 4 | `ProcessOrder_AsyncNotification_IsSent` | Sleepy Test | **Flaky + slow** â€” slows the suite and may fail under load |
| 5 | `ProcessOrder_EmptyOrder_ThrowsValidationError` | Exception Handling | Quick fix â€” just swap to `Assert.ThrowsException` |
| 6 | `GetOrderSummary_ReturnsFormattedString` | Sensitive Equality | Quick fix â€” assert on properties not `ToString()` |
| 7 | `CalculateTotal_ReturnsCorrectAmount` | Magic Numbers + Roulette | Readability â€” add named constants and messages |
| 8 | `OrderProcessor_FullWorkflow_Succeeds` | Eager Test | Add focused unit tests alongside this workflow test |
| 9 | Class-level `_logger` | General Fixture | Cleanup â€” just delete unused field |

Items 1â€“4 are the most urgent because they cause **false passes** or **flaky failures** â€” the suite looks green but isn't actually protecting you.
